body:
Are there any extensions of Riemann-Stieltjes integration that are able to handle the following integral? $\int_0^1 \alpha \space  d\alpha$ where $
\alpha(x) = \left\{  \begin{array}{lr}
   0 & x < \frac{1}{2} 
\\ \frac{1}{2} & x = \frac{1}{2}
\\ 1 & x > \frac{1}{2}
\end{array} \right.
$ Everything I've found so far have strong requirements about the funcions' continuity, and are undefined when there are shared discontinuities, even for such a simple function. My interest: Where integration by parts hold. What consequence/uses would there be to it?
